(3) Agree, but ... speaking personally, I know that most of what I say to these individuals is too far over their Neanderthal-like heads for them to be insulted by.  I also anticipate such clever retorts as &quot;OMG U R gae&quot; and &quot;U SuXXorz, n00b&quot;.  These obvious displays of a compromised intellect and lacking personality entertain me.  <br>
<br>
The greatest image I get, however, is thinking of a seventeen year old virgin sitting at his mom's computer feeding his unhealthy obsession with a cartoon character in a video game.  His interaction with others is limited to his aggressive attempts to destroy them in this game, and his ego and self image is dependant on this.  He trolls the boards here trying to get the same effect, but runs into people that are NOT like him, so he is repeatedly outsmarted and removed (trust me, this is only slightly easier than taking a shit).  The really fun part is that we know that no matter what we say or do to him, he will keep coming back!  The ugly truth is that he is truly THAT MUCH of a pathetic looser!  He wants, dare I say NEEDS us to make fun of him and slam him at every opportunity.  <br>
As a result of his failed attempts to get laid, usually followed up by the worst humiliation possible as punishment for his mere attempt, and his repeated abuse at the hands of those he thinks are his friends (but are using him for their abuse the same as we are using him for ours), he has come to associate these with attention, and has grown reliant on them.  I have no problem with this, seeing as how I enjoy kicking him just to see how far he will go before snapping back for another boot, but I also have no problem with him being banned.  Another aspect of my enjoyment is thinking of him sitting at his mom's computer jacking off to net-porn while yelling at her to &quot;leave him alone please&quot; and registering EZ Board account after account so he can come in and be banned again.  <br>
At least the soccer ball doesn't have a choice.  This guy is better than Daffy Duck in the Bugs Bunny cartoons.<br>
